# how to install R Studio on Ubuntu 22.04

# After installing R:

# from the link https://linuxhint.com/install-r-and-rstudio-ubuntu/

# RStudio is an IDE used for running codes written in R language. 
# To install RStudio on Ubuntu 22.04, you will require the following steps.

# Execute the following command to download the RStudio deb package on Ubuntu 22.04:
wget https://download1.rstudio.org/electron/jammy/amd64/rstudio-2022.12.0-353-amd64.deb # link from  https://posit.co/download/rstudio-desktop/
# Now use the following command to run the RStudio installation using dpkg.
sudo dpkg -i rstudio-2022.12.0-353-amd64.deb
# This will install  RStudio on Ubuntu.

# to run rstudio from terminal:
# find the program:
whereis rstudio  # you get the path
# example  -->  rstudio: /usr/lib/rstudio
cd /usr/lib/rstudio
./rstudio

# you can run it also from Ubuntu GUI.


